{
  "stem": "17761.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We used also to play with a wheel that we used with a little stick to run and to see who can run farther.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We had our little cheder games, like to make little squares, who ends the square, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And Shabbat, it was-- in addition to what is a regular Shabbat [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] program, we used to go-- I used to go to my grand-grandfather, Chaim Eisenthal, who was a very big erudite.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he was a [NON-ENGLISH], which was a very famous person that time in Poland.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he used to test me, to examine me if I remember what I studied in the cheder, if I know that well.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And at the end, he used to give me-- he had this little shop next to his house.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He could go in from the house.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He went to the shop and took out a red candy.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "You don't know what taste has such a candy.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That was the recompense when I knew well.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Even if I didn't know so well, also I got the candy.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Shabbos, like in any Jewish house, we kept strictly Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And usually, especially in the summertime, I-- for the [NON-ENGLISH] I went to the-- we went all to the grandfather.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he at that time, we liked very much strawberries, but not for that you buy here at the grocery stores, but strawberries that been picked up in the woods, little strawberries.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This with cream cheese or with sour cream, that was a real pleasure.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we added a lot of sugar on that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Like today, except one thing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't know there what is cholent.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Cholent was a totally different story.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
